One of the most atmospherically eerie works of American horror cinema, the film garnered a significant cult following years after being released in 1962, and is essential for every horror collection.

He follows his dream girl, Vivian Benton, on an ocean liner, where cocktails laced with a "love potion" work their magic. He then loses his fortune in the market crash and feels he has also lost the girl. This musical romantic comedy features music by Irving Berlin and an early appearance of Bing Crosby. Starring Douglas Fairbanks, this film is not to be confused with his silent of the same title from 1917.

programme.title: The Haunted House
programme.desc: Minton and Max run a counterfeiting ring out of a haunted house that they've been using as a hideout.

programme.title: Lady from Chungking
programme.desc: A young woman (Anna May Wong, the first Chinese-American movie star) leads a revolt against the occupying troops when the Japanese invade China during World War II. She’ll do anything to win; she’ll even assume the identity of an aristocrat to woo a Japanese general if she thinks it will help the cause. This Poverty Row drama also stars Harold Huber, Mae Clark, and Rick Vallin, with direction by William Nigh (Black Dragons, Doomed to Die).

programme.title: Queen of the Amazons
programme.desc: A woman ventures into the deep jungle to find her missing husband when she discovers that he has been captured by a savage all-female tribe.

programme.title: Bulldog Courage (1935)

First, he’s ‘Slim’ Braddock, a miner who turns to robbing stagecoaches after being swindled by a banker. When Slim is murdered, his son Tim, also played by McCoy, seeks vengeance. Directed by B-movie legend Sam Newfield for Excelsior Pictures, this film is a showcase for McCoy, who appeared in more than 90 movies and in 1960 earned a star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame!

programme.title: Billy the Kid Trapped (1942)
programme.desc: HIS TOMBSTONE WAS SET...But Billy Refused To Die!! Billy (Buster Crabbe) thinks luck is on his side when he and two buddies are rescued from the gallows. Unfortunately, Jim Stanton (Glenn Strange), the boss of Mesa City, plans to frame them for a series of robberies and murders. Stanton has even hired three professional killers and disguised them as Billy and his sidekicks. All goes well until the imposters foolishly try to match bullets with The Kid! Also starring Al St. John as Fuzzy, it’s the sort of movie where a character drawls, “Make one move and you'll wake up playin' a harp.”

programme.title: The Gospel According to St. Matthew

Through initially friendly to the group, this tropical island is not what it appears, and Balleau's true devises are revealed. Will any of these young adventurers survive? Or will the sadistic hunter live to kill another day? Find out in Ralph Brooke's, Bloodlust!

programme.title: I'm From Driftwood
programme.desc: Laverne Cox: I'm From Mobile/New Teacher Encounters Homophobia In Second Week/Coming Out Again To Grandma With Alzheimer's/Gender Bending And Runway Walking In A McDonald's Parking Lot/Homeless, Transgender And Finding Her Way/Trans Woman Sacrifices Everything To Finally Be Herself/Transgender High School Student Encounters Cyberbullying/A Broken Down Car, Matching Tattoos, And A Love Story/Agender Person Goes From Being Bullied In The Newark Projects To Gracing The Cover of French Vogue/ Alan Cumming: True Bisexual Stories S1 E1-10 | Laverne Cox remembers the bullying she experienced as a child, and how it's similar to the transphobia she experiences as an adult. Alexa moved from New York City to small-town Jackson, Mississippi, to teach at an under-priveleged school. After only two weeks in, Alexa had to challenge homophobia in the hallway, and had some surprising success. Megan's grandma was supportive and excited when she found out Megan was a lesbian. But after showing signs of Alzheimer's, Megan's grandma forgot and kept asking her if she was seeing any special boy. Megan received a special phone call from her grandma, though, that she'll remember forever. Jacob Tobia, activist for genderqueer, gender non-conforming, and transgender issues, bought a single pair of black pumps while organizing a Gender Nonconforming Day for their high school, a small act that would change the course of their life. After being kicked out of her home at 17, Angela Louis struggled with homelessness, abusive relationships, sex work, and depression, all while transitioning, but nothing could stop her from finding her own path and earning her diploma. Mila Jam had it all, or so she thought. Her drag persona, Britney Houston, had a massive YouTube following and she performed on a hit TV show in London. But she gave it all up so that she could finally live her truth as a woman and as herself. Olivia Page was brave enough to transition in high school. Unfortunately, a classmate decided to cyberbully her on Facebook. Olivia also had the support and kindness of a teacher who helped her through high school. A wild series of events led Sam to meeting the love of her life. Andre J. wants to tell you one thing: Love Yourself. That's how Andre went from being bullied in the projects to appearing on the cover of French Vogue. Alan Cumming remembers when he first felt an attraction to guys and how he came out to American media in a big way. - Externals

programme.title: Drag Kids
programme.desc: Drag has always been about breaking down barriers and daring to do the unexpected. Now, a new type of queen is on the scene: she’s fierce, she’s living in a time of unprecedented access to queer culture, and she’s younger than ever before. She’s a drag kid and she’s a long way from the era of the queens who led the Stonewall Riots nearly 50 years ago. Stephan, Jason, Bracken and Nemis have never met, but they’re united by a shared passion for drag. They are about to come together for the first time – to perform Lady Gaga’s ‘Born This Way’ at the world-famous Montreal Pride Festival. As they prepare for the big show, each faces their own unique challenges, as well as challenges they have in common - deep feelings of isolation and the struggle of trying to claim a place of your own on the fringes of a fringe culture. Drag Kids is a beautiful, daring, and touching portrait of four kids chasing freedom and friendship through the art of drag.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

Mother's Little Helpers is a funny, dysfunctional family drama, based on true lies, about how family ties can twist and tear you - and though they may not break you, they might send you to prison. It explores the "OK, Boomer" relationship between the free love generation and those left behind to clean up the mess.

programme.desc: This award-winning documentary explores the on and offstage lives of eight hard-working drag entertainers. Follow Carmen Carrera, Latrice Royale, and other performers as they search for love, family, and acceptance in an industry built on big hair, big dreams and illusion.

programme.title: The Walk-In Closet
programme.desc: S1 E1-4 | Dana delivers a big package. Sterling receives some very, very scary news./Sterling is very, very sad and drunk; Billie does a Drew Barrymore impression. They come up with a plan!/ It's Billie's straight brother Dom's birthday!/It's time for the first real test! Billie and Sterling meet Ms. Hutchcroft, the immigration official.

programme.title: Dropping The Soap
programme.desc: 2017 Emmy Winner, Jane Lynch, Best Actress in Web Series/Comedy. Shit's about to get real for the cast and crew of the long running (awful) soap opera "Collided Lives" when new Executive Producer Olivia Vanderstein arrives to shake things up.

programme.title: Is Written
programme.desc: The story of a poor boy whose biggest dream is to be a filmmaker. A trajectory of sufferings, struggles, victories and defeats. This story comes to show us that dreams are untouchable and worth fighting for.

programme.title: To Be Me
programme.desc: To Be Me tells the story of a young, mid-western African American who struggles with their gender identity. Played by Kate Rose Wilburn, a non-binary trans female, along with Emmy award winning actor Kim Estes as their father, this Revry Original series is here to shed light on the under represented and supported subject of gender identity.

programme.title: Equality U
programme.desc: Equality U is a feature-length documentary following 34 young activists on the Soulforce Equality Ride. At some stops they're welcomed with open arms, at others they're arrested for trespassing or for simply attempting to open up a dialog. At every stop, they're connecting with young people who've often never met an openly gay, lesbian, bisexual or transgender person who is comfortable with who they are.

programme.title: America In Transition
programme.desc: S1 E1 | After growing up misunderstood in India, Nina fell in love with another trans woman in the United States. Facing the threat of deportation, Nina and her love continue to fight for space to live and flourish when no place feels safe.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S3 E5 | In this episode of The Q Agenda, we're joined by Mexican artist Juan Solis who combines Latin Culture with LGBTQ Pride. Fashion Designer Ali Flores of Olmos y Flores talks about innovating masculine fashion. Also, music sensation Tatiana Hazel on fashion and black trans lives.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S3 E6 | In this episode of The Q Agenda, actor and musician Terrell Carter tell his incredible story of a uniquely dysfunctional family in the book Problem Child. Plus, Jorge Gutierrez of Familia: The Trans Liberation Movement, and we discuss our backgrounds to better understand the LGBTQ Community's relationship with organized religion.

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Denial
programme.desc: DENIAL is a documentary about electricity, identity, family, and about the many ways we lie to ourselves when faced with overwhelming facts. It is the story of a family coming to terms with complex personal truths against the backdrop of a global crisis.

programme.title: Suicide Kale
programme.desc: While having lunch with another couple, new couple Jasmine and Penny stumble upon an anonymous suicide note and proceed to work to uncover the identity of the author.

programme.title: The Walk-In Closet
programme.desc: S1 E1-4 | Dana delivers a big package. Sterling receives some very, very scary news./Sterling is very, very sad and drunk; Billie does a Drew Barrymore impression. They come up with a plan!/ It's Billie's straight brother Dom's birthday!/It's time for the first real test! Billie and Sterling meet Ms. Hutchcroft, the immigration official.

programme.title: The QueerX Awards
programme.desc: The circus is in town and just in time for National Coming Out Day! Welcome to the 2021 QueerX Awards brought to you by Lexus. Join us as hosts, Drew Droege and Raneir Pollard, take us on a carnival tour of LGBTQ music, films, and icons! Featuring appearances by Bowen Yang, Michaela Jaé Rodriguez, Patton Oswalt, Dwyane Wade, Erica Wheeler, and Elvira, Mistress of the Dark, Cassandra Peterson. And don’t miss the special performances by Chanel and the Circus, Mila Jam, and Alsace Carcione.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: Culture Q is the world’s first weekly queer-centric news series brought to you by the leading global queer streaming network, Revry. This innovative, weekly news series creatively features entertainment, pop culture, lifestyle and political news with wit and insightfully nuanced perspectives. Emphasizing the queer millieu, Culture Q stands to be the leading, weekly forum for boundary-pushing discussions and commentary. Hosted by digital news influencer pioneers, Shira Lazar and Andy Lalwani of the highly successful What’s Trending, Culture Q will feature an ever-changing cavalcade of guests who help capture that X-factor which defines queer culture.

programme.title: No Gender! The Queer Life Of An Intersex Manga Artist
programme.desc: Up until age 30, Sho Arai lived as a woman, but was found to be intersex after chromosome testing.

programme.title: The Influencers
programme.desc: Six social media influencers compete for an exclusive brand deal with the latest millennial juice craze: Jücytox. As cameras capture each influencer IRL, the manicured versions they present to the world online begin to not just crumble, but implode before our eyes.

programme.title: Strut
programme.desc: In each episode of Strut, we watch Eddie and her friends transform through their risky new endeavor in unexpected positive ways. Eddie is a geeky porn editor whose low self-confidence has turned her into a 26-year-old hermit. Her friends, Eva (an unemployed artist), Lucy (an intern), and Chandaleer (a trainwreck/fashion model) vow to save her from her unhealthy solitude. When the friends decide to start a high-end escorting agency to earn more money, they convince skeptical Eddie to help them build their business and lift her self-esteem. Together they successfully navigate the adrenaline-fueled escorting industry with Eddie as their CEO and fellow sex worker.

programme.title: Never Quit
programme.desc: This is a victorious story of a female athlete whose rise to stardom and popularity suddenly misses the shot. Discover how we don't always understand the Lord’s plan, but realize everything happens for a reason.

programme.title: Moving Stories
programme.desc: A film, by Rob Fruchtman, Cornelia Ravenal, Mikael Södersten, Wendy Sax Six, about diverse dancers from the acclaimed Battery Dance Company who travel the world, working with youth who have experienced war, poverty, prejudice, sexual exploitation, and severe trauma as refugees. In India they work with girls rescued from sex trafficking and gender violence; in Romania, with gypsy kids from one of Europe's worst slums; in South Korea, with young North Koreans who risked their lives to escape; and in Iraq, with a gifted young Muslim dancer, fighting to survive. Incredibly, they have just one week to teach the tools of choreography and collaboration to kids who may be enemies, who may have been abused, who may be suspicious and fearful, so that they can create dances to perform for their communities. As they struggle to break through, the dancer-teachers confront their own frustrations. Yet their students respond in extraordinary ways - and as they prepare to perform in public in what seems an impossibly short time, both students and teachers experience surprising transformations, unlocking feelings and stories in wellsprings of creativity.

programme.title: My Trans Life
programme.desc: Being trans is a mental, physical and emotional journey and MY TRANS LIFE showcases inspiring trans individuals on their journeys of acceptance. From preparing for major surgery, to tackling love lives, to campaigning for equality, MY TRANS LIFE follows transgender people facing the world in the body they were meant to be in.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S3 E7 | In this episode of The Q Agenda, influencer Tony Directs describes coming out to his audience. Trailblazing actress Candis Cayne talks about performing and dating as a transgender woman. Plus, an important discussion on the Supreme Court Ruling that the Civil Rights Act protects LGBTQ people from job discrimination.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S3 E8 | In this episode, actress Alexandra Grey of Empire chats with Juliana about her incredible life story and trans representation in entertainment. Bamby Salcedo of the TransLatin@ Coalition highlights the important work she's doing for the community and a discussion on asexuality. All that and more on The Q Agenda!

programme.title: Coming of Age in Cherry Grove
programme.desc: Founded in 1869, Cherry Grove (Fire Island, NY) is considered by most to be the first openly LGBTQ community in the United States. It has become known as one of the most accepting resort communities in the world – a place where you can not only discover who you are, but also freely experiment with who or what (gender) you may want to become. Cherry Grove is also known for the famous “INVASION” – an annual ritual that takes place every July 4th as a celebration of gender acceptance. This film tells the stories of a variety of long-term residents and what they find so wonderful about life in Cherry Grove.

programme.title: CONTRACORRIENTE
programme.desc: Miguel is a fisherman in a tiny Peruvian village where traditions run deep. He is married to the lovely Mariela and about to be a father, but has a secret love affair with Santiago, a painter, who is ostracized by the town because he's gay. After a tragic accident occurs, Miguel must choose between sentencing Santiago to eternal torment or doing right by him and, in turn, revealing their relationship to Mariela and the entire village.

programme.title: DIA NARANJA
programme.desc: Three Latin American women from different backgrounds see their fantasies about the future give way to anxiety as they are hit with the same shocking news: they are pregnant. A colorful, vivacious look at the excitement and drama that often accompanies the prospect of motherhood.

programme.title: CAMINO DEL VINO
programme.desc: Tragedy befalls a world-famous sommelier attending an important wine event when he suddenly, inexplicably loses his palate. His mission to recover his talent leads him on a journey through peerless wineries and beautiful vineyards, but most importantly into his own soul.

programme.title: CAPTAIN ORELLANA
programme.desc: Captain Orellana, a private investigator and former cop specializing in the most impossible mysteries, is tapped for the wackiest, most dangerous case of his long career. With a comical 007-like swagger, Orellna gets to the bottom of the uncanny occurrences in a remote village that seems to be ? POSSESSED!

programme.title: OMNIVORES
programme.desc: A prestigious journalist accepts an undercover writing assignment addressing the recent emergence of "clandestine restaurants," one of which holds secret gatherings where diners feast on human flesh in exchange for large sums of money. What started as a simple job may just end in a bloody nightmare.

programme.title: RABBIT WOMAN
programme.desc: A China-born state employee discovers corruption within the Argentinian police force and bravely sets out to bring an end to its corrupt ties to the Chinese mafia. While on the run from the criminals, she discovers a bizarre animal experiment involving rabbits that perversely may hold the key to her success.

programme.title: Canada Cultivation and Mushroom Editing
programme.desc: In early May, we had Mydecine (NEO: MYCO) (OTCMKTS: MYCOF) CSO Rob Roscow on the Dales Report to talk about their 2a clinical trials. Today we have Damon Michaels with us to discuss some of the recent news that’s come out for Mydecine including Health Canada’s approval of the expansion of their cultivation facilities here in Canada. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - Canadian expansion means that Mydecine has “instant access” and allows them to supply clinical trials says Michaels - - The possibility of editing mushrooms - - Mydecine facility in Canada probably won’t scale to meet a commercial need, says Michaels - - The roadmap for the next 12 months? Proving efficacy and safety – and looking at protocols

programme.title: How the Psychedelic Industry Can Help Mental Health
programme.desc: Last month we had Dr. Mike Hart for an interview with The Dales Report. Dr. Hart is the Host of Heart to Hart Podcast and a medical doctor at the Ready To Go Clinic, offering treatments to patients that involve cannabis and ketamine. We’re thrilled to have Hart back with us again to discuss the different psychedelic compounds and how they can impact mental health, plus how the industry is benefitting from cannabis’ legalization. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - The psychedelic molecule psilocybin affects mental health in part by breaking up your default mode network - - Psychedelics’ perception benefitting from cannabis’ legalization - - Both cannabis and psychedelic compounds have an impact on empathy and improved mental health - - COVID and financial worry is taking a toll

programme.title: MDMA-Assisted Therapy for PTSD
programme.desc: A new report just released this week by Nature Medicine has a lot of players in both medicine and the psychedelics industry talking. MDMA and other psychedelics like psilocybin have been under scrutiny lately as a possible avenue of treatment for not only PTSD but mental health issues generally. Dr. Mike Hart is back to chat again with us about that report on MDMA-Assisted therapy for severe PTSD. programme.title: Freeing the Prisoners of the War on Drugs
programme.desc: In 1971, President Richard Nixon called for a “war on drugs”. His rhetoric set in motion decades of policies that unjustly targeted black and brown Americans and spurred cycles of incarceration directly impacting millions of lives and families. Today, at the same time that multi-state cannabis companies celebrate exponential growth and millions in revenue, people are still languishing behind bars for cannabis offenses. As corporate America and mainstream markets turn their eyes to cannabis, advocates worry that the plight of those victimized by an unjust system will be forgotten. What kind of policies do Americans need to see included in proposed federal legalization to start repairing the damage done by the war on drugs? What responsibility do for-profit companies have to supporting efforts to free prisoners of the war on drugs? Does a shift from punitive to restorative justice ensure that we avoid repeating the mistakes of the past?

programme.title: How the Psychedelic Industry Can Help Mental Health

Dr. Hart is the Host of Heart to Hart Podcast and a medical doctor at the Ready To Go Clinic, offering treatments to patients that involve cannabis and ketamine. We’re thrilled to have Hart back with us again to discuss the different psychedelic compounds and how they can impact mental health, plus how the industry is benefitting from cannabis’ legalization. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - The psychedelic molecule psilocybin affects mental health in part by breaking up your default mode network - - Psychedelics’ perception benefitting from cannabis’ legalization - - Both cannabis and psychedelic compounds have an impact on empathy and improved mental health - - COVID and financial worry is taking a toll

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: South Africa
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa knows that an adventurous safari is a wonderful way to experience South Africa. Get up-close-and-personal with lions, giraffes, elephants, and dozens of other animals in their natural habitat, thanks to robust preservation laws in place.

programme.title: Edinburgh and the Scottish Highlands
programme.desc: Climb the ramparts of Edinburgh Castle. Tee up at the world's most famous golf course, St. Andrews. Tour Deward's whiskey distillery. Stroll Stirling's historic battlefields of Braveheart fame. And, sail the bonny banks of legendary Loch Lomond.

programme.title: London
programme.desc: Rudy answers London's call with an expert tour of its traditional sights and contemporary, cutting-edge attractions. In London's breathtaking countryside you will find mythic castles, the real Alice in Wonderland's candy store, Jane Austen's house, and the mysterious megaliths of Stonehenge.

programme.title: Uzbekistan
programme.desc: In one of his series' most colorful episodes, Maxa takes viewers along the Silk Road in a country that is an emerging economy in Central Asia, Uzbekistan. Marvel at eye-popping mosques built centuries ago, and Rudy joins a family for the preparation of the national dish of "plov."

programme.title: Cape Town
programme.desc: Cape Town is a nexus of cultures in a setting so stunning it is called “Africa's Riviera." Where else in the world can you wake up in a cosmopolitan city, spend the afternoon with penguins, ride a funicular to the edge of the continent, and watch the sun set from a beach with a glass of wine?

programme.title: Garden Route
programme.desc: The Garden Route takes you along a rugged, gorgeous South African coastline. Surfers brave enormous waves and exotic birds watch visitors climb serpentine paths that rise above the coast amid seaside resort towns. Also, visit South Africa's lush wine country in the village of Franschhoek.

programme.title: Korea
programme.desc: From the bustling city of Seoul with its 10 million residents to the country's quite countryside, South Korea is a traveler’s paradise. With their misty mountain temples and the uber-modern cities, Koreans mix an abiding sense if history and traditions with a zeal to achieve global success.

programme.title: Best of the National Parks
programme.desc: Each year millions from around the world visit America's national parks, lured by images of lands of wonder beyond expression. This exhilarating program reveals the very best locations in America’s national parks to gaze at geysers, spot wildlife, mountain climb, spelunk, and even tie the knot.

programme.title: Germany's Via Julia
programme.desc: Discover the ancient Roman military road Via Julia that made rapid travel from Lutetia (now Paris) to Constantinople (now Istanbul) possible. Meet the people who keep the memories of this ancient route intact, and who do their utmost to keep the sacred traditions of their ancestors alive.

programme.title: The Road of Money: Mexico to the U.S.A.
programme.desc: Upon landing in Mexico centuries ago the Spanish immediately found silver. The Spanish then constructed a road 3,000 km long to transport the silver from the mines, a road full of hopes, but also riddled with pitfalls and danger. Explore this ancient road from Mexico to the southern United States.

programme.title: The Bahamas - The Heart of the Ocean
programme.desc: As the first lands of the New World to be discovered by Europeans, the Bahamas have always attracted sailors and adventurers. Fed by the warm, nutrient-rich currents of the Gulf Stream, their shallow waters offer today's travelers a crystal-clear sea teeming with marine life.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Puebla, Where the Good Cooks Are From
programme.desc: Puebla, Mexico: According to Tony, the best line cooks in NYC come from Mexico, so he travels to the Puebla, and enjoys mole sauces, toasted ant eggs, fried worms, and the legendary pulque (a slightly hallucinogenic drink made from cactus sap).

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Best Parks to Escape the Crowds
programme.desc: Some of the best national parks attract thousands of spectators every day. If you're looking for a place to go where you won't bump elbows, then take a look at these solitary parks.

programme.title: Best Parks to Get Wet & Wild
programme.desc: From the most scenic drive in America, to the world's largest bowl of fresh water, these parks have the wettest landscape for your pleasure.

programme.title: S8E2 - Tijuana Taco Crawl
programme.desc: Three local Tijuana foodies take Rick on a taco crawl. Experience arrachera tacos, suadero tacos, sauteed and fried shrimp tacos, steamed tacos, and smoked salmon tacos. At home, Rick creates a taco feast for a casual backyard cookout.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Amsterdam
programme.desc: Whether by foot, bike, or boat, Laura hits all the hotspots in Amsterdam, such as the Rijksmuseum and the Hotel De L'Europe. She even takes a day-trip outside the city to explore neighboring Volendam and picturesque Volendam Harbor and drops into the Rembrandt Hoeve Cheesefarm and Clog Factory.

programme.title: Rome
programme.desc: Rudy is in the city where all roads lead - Roma. We begin in ancient Rome - the Forum, Palatine Hill, Colosseum, and the Baths of Caracalla. Then, we explore the modern city of Rome with its ambient life in the streets, cafes, pizzerias and gelaterias.

programme.title: Brisbane Queensland
programme.desc: It is all about the great outdoors as Jason visits Kangaroo Point, has fun kayaking with the Riverlife Adventure Centre crew, gets up close with endangered koala bears, and takes a trip to the zoo.

programme.title: S8E6 - Palestine
programme.desc: Exploring Palestine — the Muslim and Arab half of the Holy Land — we'll visit Jerusalem, harvest olives near Ramallah, follow pilgrims to Bethlehem, and bob in the Dead Sea.

programme.title: Part 2
programme.desc: Travel to the Pinar del Rio and visit the lush tobacco fields that produce the most sought-after cigars in the world. As you explore further, colorful towns and sugar plantations unfold before your eyes. Walk the beaches of Matanzas and Cuba’s colorful coastline. Cuban people welcome visitors with open arms, and their blend of cultures overflow with friendly and easy-going hospitality.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: The New Frontier
programme.desc: Dive into the polar abyss of Greenland’s fjords, testing the limits of man’s ability to survive beneath Arctic waters. This expedition explores of 800 miles of Greenland’s coasts, 450 Arctic dives, and researching over 1,000 scientific hypotheses with guidance by the local Inuit population.

programme.title: Ganvie
programme.desc: Welcome to Ganvie, land of the unsubdued, the free, the resistance, and of peaceful waters. In Ganvie, the Tofinu people live on the water. To do so they must move at a careful pace, learn to live without excess, and form deep bonds of family and friendship to survive.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: London
programme.desc: London has played a key role in world affairs for centuries, and as you stroll throughout this magnificent city, history comes to life before your eyes. Buckingham Palace, Campden Market, Covent Garden, the Tower of London, and Cliveden House are just the beginning of the places you will visit.

programme.title: Amsterdam
programme.desc: Whether by foot, bike, or boat, Laura hits all the hotspots in Amsterdam, such as the Rijksmuseum and the Hotel De L'Europe. She even takes a day-trip outside the city to explore neighboring Volendam and picturesque Volendam Harbor and drops into the Rembrandt Hoeve Cheesefarm and Clog Factory.

programme.title: Cambodia
programme.desc: Cambodia has recently risen as a must-see travel destination, and top-notch resorts and hotels have developed to accommodate travelers. Join Laura as she treks to the magnificent temples of Angkor Wat, Bayon, and Ta Prohm via one of Asia's most recognizable animals - the elephant.

programme.title: The Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Begin your stay along the Amalfi Coast in stunning Positano. They say Ravello is a town suspended between sea and sky, and it will leave an impression on you as it has on many artists, musicians, and writers. In Salerno, the gardens at Villa Rufolo will seer into your memory.

programme.title: Saigon
programme.desc: Saigon, Vietnam is an incredible place to visit. It has history, and cultural excursions, like cruising the Mekong Delta and visiting a floating marketplace. In Ho Chi Minh City you can shop until you drop, stay in five-star hotels, and enjoy an incredible culinary experience.

programme.title: Auckland
programme.desc: Auckland is New Zealand's largest city. Laura takes an hour's drive south of Auckland to a working sheep farm in the New Zealand countryside. A few miles down the road, Laura spies a familiar sight - Hobbiton, the set from the Lord of the Rings films where Bilbo lived before and after his journey.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Tahiti and Bora Bora
programme.desc: For sheer tropical splendor, the islands of Tahiti and Bora Bora stand alone. Hyper blue lagoons, white-sand beaches, fish of every shape, size, and color, as well as a generous and welcoming people make these islands key destinations for travelers from around the world.

programme.title: Polynesia
programme.desc: Experience Polynesia’s rich sea life, crystal blue waters, and vibrant cultures. Tour the diverse reefs of the coral, sea turtle rehabilitation centers, and the many islands and atolls. Participate in the oyster-cultivation process at the major pearl farm, and tour dramatic Marquesas Islands.

programme.title: Montreal
programme.desc: Two of the most unique cities in the world are just north of New England. Here you will find brie, pate, jewel box-patisseries, and “s’il vous plait” right along with bagels, maple syrup, hockey, delis, and bocce ball. Those who forged Montreal and Quebec City braved much to see them flourish.

programme.title: Nova Scotia & Newfoundland
programme.desc: From the charming fishing towns of Nova Scotia to the vast wilderness of Newfoundland, explore the last great open spaces of Eastern North America. A touch of New England, a dash of Germany, here a British fort, there an Irish brogue, the area was peopled by the descendants of hardy colonists.

programme.title: Food, Drink, & Culture
programme.desc: In Istanbul’s Spice Market, brown-gold paprika is carefully molded into pyramids. Cinnamon, cumin, ginger, and cardamom infuse the air. From haggis in Scotland to soba and tea in Japan, from asada in Argentina to bibimbap in Korea, food and drink help illustrate the culture and people of a location.

programme.title: Asian Cities
programme.desc: From the world’s largest city, Tokyo, to the colorful chaos of Delhi, and from the modern miracle of Seoul to the teeming streets of Bangkok, this is your passport to the high-tech marvels and back-street secrets of four of the world’s most amazing cities Asian Cities.

programme.title: Travel Thru History
programme.desc: In this episode we visit the Kennedy Space Center located on Florida's famous Space Coast. We will speak to NASA engineers about the past, present and future of American space travel, as well as take a look at the attractions K.S.C. has to offer.

programme.title: Yellowstone: America's First National Park
programme.desc: Vast, beautiful, and untamed, Yellowstone's wilderness ignites the imagination like no other national park. Get a ringside seat for the geothermal wonders, geyser gazing, and diversity of wildlife that gave Yellowstone the nickname, "America's Serengeti."

programme.title: Italy's Via Cassia
programme.desc: Italy’s Via Cassia once led north from Rome to Florence, finally joining the Via Aurelia at Luna (now Luni). As you meander northward along the ancient route, each unique location you visit, and the interesting people you meet there, speak vividly to the region’s steeped history and culture.

programme.title: Ecuador: The Road of a New World
programme.desc: In 2007, with the election of President Rafael Correa, the people of Ecuador chose a new way of building towards the future based on the Quechua Indian philosophy of “living well” that focuses on living in harmony with ones’ self, with other people, with nature, and with the Earth.

programme.title: The Bahamas - The Heart of the Ocean
programme.desc: As the first lands of the New World to be discovered by Europeans, the Bahamas have always attracted sailors and adventurers. Fed by the warm, nutrient-rich currents of the Gulf Stream, their shallow waters offer today's travelers a crystal-clear sea teeming with marine life.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Los Angeles, My Own Heart of Darkness
programme.desc: Los Angeles, CA: New York chef, Anthony Bourdain, descends into the culinary underbelly of his metropolitan nemesis, Los Angeles, where he experiences the trials of celebrity fame and the joys of West Coast cuisine.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Best Parks to Star in Your Own Western
programme.desc: Want to release your inner cowboy? These are the western capitals of the world. From the wild buffalo to the beautiful sunsets, these are the best parks ever to star in your own western.

programme.title: Lonely Planet: Best Parks Ever - America's National Parks
programme.desc: This episode features two main attractions: beautiful sunrises and amazing waterfalls. You'll never find more stunning places for rises and falls.

programme.title: S8E3 - Cooking on the Sea of Cortez
programme.desc: Rick is always up for a cooking challenge, and after a day on the waters of the Sea of Cortez, Rick grills dinner for the group on the beach of Espiritu Santo Island. To stock up on supplies Rick shops in the La Paz market for ingredients.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Cambodia
programme.desc: Cambodia has recently risen as a must-see travel destination, and top-notch resorts and hotels have developed to accommodate travelers. Join Laura as she treks to the magnificent temples of Angkor Wat, Bayon, and Ta Prohm via one of Asia's most recognizable animals - the elephant.

programme.title: Venice
programme.desc: Venice, the city of winding canals, decadent buildings, faith, and romance. Tour Piazza San Marco and the Basilica of San Marco. Visit a mask shop, then ship off to the islands of Murano, Burano and Torcello. Venice’s very existence, floating as if on a dream, is an amazing experience to behold.

programme.title: Tasmania
programme.desc: Jason's next stop is filled with luxury, as we are treated to a relaxing spa at Freycinet National Park. We will also explore Wineglass Bay, voted one of the top 10 beaches in the entire world.

programme.title: S8E7 - Italy's Riviera: Cinque Terre
programme.desc: We'll visit Italy's five tiny seaside towns known as the Cinque Terre, while stopping to fish for anchovies, sip wine from barrels, and savor twinkling Mediterranean vistas.

programme.title: Inner Worlds
programme.desc: What other country has eaten organic food for the past 20 years, has derived 30% of its energy from renewable sources, is a pioneer in ecotourism, and has a Ministry for Climate Change? The answer is, Cuba, with 263 protected areas, including six UNESCO World Biosphere Reserves.

programme.title: Key West
programme.desc: We are on island time for this episode. Learn about the Key's treasure hunting history at the Mel Fisher Museum. Explore Fort Jefferson, an isolated fort in the Gulf of Mexico that defended the islands. American literature enthusiasts will enjoy a look at Ernest Hemingway's Key West home.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: Polar Immersion
programme.desc: Firmly beset in the grip of polar winter, an opportunity arises to study climate change above and beneath the ice sheet. Part scientific exploration, part shared existence with the Inuit, this human adventure reveals the never-before-seen depths of this fascinating world in the throes of upheaval.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Join Alexandra as she visits with a friendly, forward-thinking family in Las Vegas, Nevada, a city certainly not built on winners (unless you become one), where anything is possible, and where water is so much of a precious resource the city employs water waste investigators.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Renaissance Europe
programme.desc: Travelers adore Italy, and Italy adores the Renaissance. In this historical half-hour, we follow Western Europe's transitiical sites and museums in favor of a trip--or a day--just for fun.

programme.title: Europe's Getaways
programme.desc: A key attraction of travel on any continent, including Europe, is that 30 minutes outside any city exists a getaway unlike any you will find on the globe. Truly unique locations that resonate with history and significance. Here, we explore a few such places.

programme.title: Ireland's West Coast
programme.desc: Our trip to Ireland's west coast begins in Galway, Europe's fastest growing city, shopping for Irish crystal and Celtic jewelry. Then it is a salt-sprayed trip to the fabled Aran Islands where we reach breathless heights at a Stone Age fort and ferret out traditional hand-knit sweaters.

programme.title: Dublin and Beyond
programme.desc: Irish eyes are smiling when we explore Dublin, Ireland's urban core. There is history around every corner, and Dublin delights with Trinity College, the Book of Kells, the famous Guinness Brewery, and the infamous Kilmainham jail where Irish rebels spent their last days.

programme.title: Germany's Romantic Road
programme.desc: The Romantic Road winds through some of Germany's most picturesque countryside complete with medieval villages and Baroque Palaces. We start our journey in Wurzburg where we visit the spectacular Baroque Bishop's Palace or Residenz and taste wine at one of Wurzburg's many wine festivals.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Thailand, The Andaman Islands
programme.desc: Andaman Coast towns such as Phuket are well known to backpackers and sun seekers. Join Rudy as he paddles through hidden entrances of small islands to find mangroves few people ever see. Also, visit the dramatic limestone cliffs and rock formations jutting out from translucent waters of Phang-nga Bay.

programme.title: Estonia
programme.desc: Venture to Estonia and the islands of Saaremaa and Muhu where you will find windmills, thatch-roofed farmhouses, and quiet waters. Rudy interviews Mart Laar who took over Estonia under tough conditions following the withdrawal of Soviet troops and turned it into a dynamic country.

programme.title: St. Petersburg, Russia
programme.desc: From the splendors of Peterhof to the quiet grace of the city's canals, this former capital built by a czar has reclaimed its position as one of the world's great destinations. St. Petersburg--enjoying a renaissance since its favorite son, Vladimir Putin, ascended to office—has lifted its gloom.

programme.title: Buenos Aires, Argentina
programme.desc: The style and verve of one of South America's most beautiful capitals is highlighted with Argentina's national dance, the tango, as well as the energy that its diverse population brings to the urban landscape. Discover a very special place in Buenos Aires.

programme.title: Mendoza, Argentina
programme.desc: As Rudy ascends into the thin air of the Andes, he stops to visit the graveyard of those who died climbing Aconcagua. Rudy’s next choice for high-altitude adventure? Getting soaked whitewater rafting. Back at sea level he meets winemakers whose elegant Malbecs are shaking up the world's wine market.

programme.title: India: From Girl to Woman
programme.desc: “First marriage and then love.” This Indian proverb describes Indian society quite accurately in terms of how the tradition of marriage is perceived and experienced in the country. In India, people do not just marry whoever they wish. It is the family that decides in an arrangement called Shaadi.

programme.title: Kyoto, Japan
programme.desc: The spiritual heart of Japan, Kyoto offers a glimpse of Japanese life as it used to be, primarily because it was spared during World War II. Comfortable streets with wooden homes, impressive temples, and a dedication to ancient Japanese traditions make Kyoto one of Japan's most visited cities.

programme.title: Yosemite America's Treasure
programme.desc: Experience Yosemite's breathtaking icons like the granite monoliths El Capitan and Half Dome and behold the splendor of Bridal Veil and Yosemite Falls. Explore Yosemite's deep history as the first land set aside for preservation, and a land that inspired John Muir and photographer Ansel Adams.

programme.title: Portugal's Via Publicae
programme.desc: Open your ears to those who call this land home, and who will unveil its unique characteristics to you. Via Publicae was once an ancient Roman road and trade route that stretched from Braga in the north to Lisbon in the south of Portugal. Roman influence was once very strong in this region.

programme.title: From Ouagadougou to Conakry: The Road of Possibility
programme.desc: In Burkina Faso, Mali, and Guinea, explore the “Africa of Possibility.” This is a continent with solutions, thanks to crafty people and their capacity to adapt. The Road of Possibility is more than journey from Ouagadougou to Conakry. On these tricky roads, obstacles trigger unique encounters.

programme.title: Fiji - Island Flavors
programme.desc: The Fijian Archipelago consists of more than 300 islands scattered across the South Pacific Ocean. In Fiji, everyone can find an island that suits them, as you retrace the trail of Robinson Crusoe in this incredible paradise.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: The French Laundry Experience
programme.desc: Napa, CA: Marooned in San Francisco, Tony tastes local shellfish and durian ice cream before embarking on a pilgrimage to experience the genius of Thomas Keller, chef and owner of The French Laundry.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Mt. Rushmore and the Black Hills
programme.desc: Mount Rushmore stands unrivaled in the world, a sky-high tribute to the heroes and ideals that shaped America. This stirring program features rare footage that chronicles its monumental construction. This iconic treasure is just one of the wonders to be found in the stoic Black Hill’s region.

programme.title: S8E4 - Presenting: World-Class Wines of Baja
programme.desc: Join Rick and winemaker Hugo d’Acosta as they toast the world-class wines of Baja California Norte. Hugo first introduces Rick his Casa de Piedra wines before moving on to Tres Mujeres, L.A. Cetto, and the San Rafael Winery.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: The Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Begin your stay along the Amalfi Coast in stunning Positano. They say Ravello is a town suspended between sea and sky, and it will leave an impression on you as it has on many artists, musicians, and writers. In Salerno, the gardens at Villa Rufolo will seer into your memory.

programme.title: Genoa and the Italian Riviera
programme.desc: We are off to the Italian Riviera seeking la dolce vita in one of the world's most romantic locations. With awe-inspiring cliffs, and beaches that shimmer like jewels on the Mediterranean, the Riviera is as stunning a coastline as anywhere in Europe.

programme.title: Adelaide, Part 1
programme.desc: Spend the entire day on Kangaroo Island, as Jason gets adventurous in Adelaide. We will learn to make our own blend of wine at Penfolds, while also taking in breathtaking views as we glide over Barossa in a hot-air balloon.

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: Part 2
programme.desc: Travel to the Pinar del Rio and visit the lush tobacco fields that produce the most sought-after cigars in the world. As you explore further, colorful towns and sugar plantations unfold before your eyes. Walk the beaches of Matanzas and Cuba’s colorful coastline. Cuban people welcome visitors with open arms, and their blend of cultures overflow with friendly and easy-going hospitality.

programme.title: Savannah
programme.desc: We visit the old South and enjoy some sweet tea in Savannah. On this episode, we will stroll the city’s beautiful squares, as well as visit its civil war past at Old Fort Jackson. Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: Light Beneath the Arctic
programme.desc: Ghislain and Emmanuelle Bardout and the U.T.P. team take you on a fresh expedition through the Northwest Passage, revealing a mythical seaway that symbolizes the very evolution of the polar world. The team will dive into the “twilight zone” to find the first biofluorescent Arctic species.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Join Alexandra as she visits with a friendly, forward-thinking family in Las Vegas, Nevada, a city certainly not built on winners (unless you become one), where anything is possible, and where water is so much of a precious resource the city employs water waste investigators.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Prague
programme.desc: Explore the heart of Bohemia as we join Laura in Prague. Visit Prague Castle, the Charles Bridge, and the Jewish Quarter. Gothic Loket Castle is a short, scenic drive away from the city and worth the tour. Next up the must-see spa town of Karlovy Vary.

programme.title: Britain's Historic Countryside
programme.desc: First stops are Camden Market and Notting Hill Gate. Enjoy a treat as Laura escorts you to the birthplace of pomp and circumstance, Buckingham Palace. Then mosey down to Windsor Castle before taking on London with Big Ben and Tower Bridge.

programme.title: Ireland
programme.desc: Ireland is a country filled with tradition, culture, and history, and here you will feel outright the pride of the Celts as you visit Blarney and Ashford Castles, learn of Francis Mahoney, meet the Guinness family, and tour the Irish School of Falconry.

programme.title: Chiang-Mai
programme.desc: Explore Chiang Mai's "Night Bazaar" that hums with business, and its Buddhist Temples. When Laura visits the Maesa Elephant Camp, she is not just meeting a majestic animal, but an icon. Finally, join Laura ventures into Northern Thailand.

programme.title: Life Down Under
programme.desc: Laura McKenzie means business when she says that Queenstown is the “adventure capital of the world.” Located on the shores of beautiful Lake Wakatipu, Queenstown is surrounded by “the Remarkables,” mountains in the center of New Zealand's South Island.

programme.title: Puerto Rico
programme.desc: First, Laura will take us to San Juan, one of the largest natural harbors in the Caribbean. In Puerto Rico, the weather's warm year-round and the ocean water is heavenly. While the islands are Americanized, they also still retain their Hispanic culture.

programme.title: Italy: Part 2
programme.desc: The brilliance and grandeur of Italy is demonstrated in five captivating settings. Feel like a tall wildflower in the sun and breeze as the hills of Altomonte billow off into the distance, sooth every aching nerve as you absorb the perfect view along the Tiber River, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Kyushu
programme.desc: Explore the island of Kyushu with it's dramatic landscape and hot sands, and discover the essence of Japanese cuisine with Daisuke Utagawa and Rudy Maxa.

programme.desc: In the frigid Alaskan town of Unalakleet, the Twetos battle the arctic elements to transport supplies to some of the most inaccessible areas on the planet.

programme.title: Life or Death
programme.desc: Pilot Luke Hickerson transports dangerous chemicals from Barrow to the remote village of Atqasuk. Then the cold and dark winter claims its first casualty and Jim must make arrangements to transport the casket.

programme.title: America's Treasures: National Parks
programme.desc: A cinematic journey through the awe-inspiring landscapes, historic sites and untamed wilderness of America's most legendary outdoor playgrounds.

programme.title: United States of Sports
programme.desc: Copa90’s Eli and Timbsy and Love Island’s Josh Denzel go on a once-in-a-lifetime road trip. Then, the guys hit the Midwest for an unforgettable road trip through Detroit, Chicago and Cincinnati.

programme.title: Beef Lamb Pig
programme.desc: Guy hunts down all kinds of meaty favorites from cottage pie to Asian-barbeque in Kentucky and North Carolina.

programme.title: Big Food Small Towns
programme.desc: Guy stops in small towns to dig in to big-time eats. In Raymond, NH, a butchery cranks out scratch-made corn dogs. In Rocky Hill, NJ, a 1700s inn turned gastropub dishes out a tomato twist on burgers and a spin on disco fries.

programme.title: Mega Mouthfuls
programme.desc: Guy unhinges his jaw for some mega-mouthful meals. In Louisville, KY, a funky seafood spot piles their specialties on top of waffles, and in Portland, OR, a killer barbecue food truck stacks a fully-loaded "shabamwich."

programme.title: Burgers Buns Bagels
programme.desc: This trip, Guy's picking up everything from burgers to buns to bagels. In Portsmouth, NH, a deli serves up lamb burgers and righteous ribs. In Los Angeles, a Koreatown favorite loads up Asian buns and a unique bacon-corn bar dish.

programme.title: Something in the Water
programme.desc: Chronicles singer-songwriter Steve Azar's endeavor to record his album Down at the Liquor Store at the historic Club Ebony in Indianola, Mississippi with a group of storied musicians.

programme.title: New Mexico: True Stories
programme.desc: New Mexico is a haven for those who seek to follow their own path. See how this adventurous spirit shapes a way of life - from culture to art to cuisine and everything in between.

programme.title: America. The Beautiful.: Columbia River Gorge
programme.desc: Kayaker Rush Sturges rides life-threatening rapids and waterfalls.

programme.title: Baby Comes to Life: Burning from Within; Tara's Angels; Healed by Kindness; Dannion Brinkley
programme.desc: A baby is born lifeless and declared dead, but after 78 minutes, miraculously comes to life. A Vietnam veteran is struck by lightning while talking on the phone and is dead for the next 28 minutes. After his experience he gained the ability to predict the future and communicate with the dead.

programme.title: Paradise Lost
programme.desc: Newlyweds Ben and Joanna's happiness is short-lived when Parsons leads a pirate attack on the family. The arrival of a merchant ship rescues the Robinsons. Back in Boston, David stands trial for the murder of Parson's brother.

programme.title: Heads you Lose
programme.desc: During the French Revolution, while working as a servant in the Chateau of Pierre Mandin in 1792, Jess is forced to serve Pierre's buffoonish, drunken son, Phillipe. With the threat of the Republicans increasing, Phillipe is disguised as a servant, and experiences life from a new perspective.

programme.title: The Runaway
programme.desc: It is 1850. Jess befriends 16-year-old Samuel, who is expected to take over his deceased father's job as the village baker. Samuel dreams of travelling the world and “being somebody.” At the spur of the moment, Samuel decides to run away with a minstrel troupe to travel the world.

programme.title: Breakdown
programme.desc: With Oregon in their sights, Dylan openly challenges Brock’s decision to escape Chicago for a simpler life in Oregon. Just when smoother roads appear to be prevailing, something profoundly mysterious occurs that changes the Turner's plans.

programme.title: Breakthrough
programme.desc: When things appear to be going from bad to worse, God’s miraculous energy inspires Dylan to contemplate his depth of faith. The question is, will Brock and Dylan together discover the power that God’s love has to cast away all fear?

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis goes for a spin in a Lincoln Cosmo and Model A Rod.

programme.title: Escape into Fear
programme.desc: William and the rebels suspect Xax is plotting with Kreel who has a reputation of delivering powerful, dark magic. After Princess Vara escapes during a battle with Xaxian warriors, William is conflicted when he discovers that there is a bounty on his head that also threatens the villagers.

programme.title: Master of Doubt
programme.desc: During a hunt with a group of Warriors, Xax is ecstatic to cross paths with Will and his rebel forces. After they are chased by the horsemen on an open plain with seemingly no escape, the mist clears and reveals a mysterious castle. But the group soon discovers that this is no ordinary castle.

programme.title: Resurrection
programme.desc: With the apparent death of Kalem, the band splits up. Kreel assures Xax that the battle to win the Kingdom has been won. William has banished himself to a life of solitude, working on a pig farm. But after Kalem appears to him again, William sets out for one more chance to find the Crystal Arrow.

programme.title: A Cat and Mouse Game
programme.desc: A family and their cat, Marcel, encounter a pet mouse (Cheeky) left behind by the former residents of a summer cottage. Like the classic comedy series, “Tom and Jerry”, Marcel watches and attempts to capture the mischievous Cheeky who constantly eludes him. What will become of the chase in time?

programme.title: Made for Each Other
programme.desc: Newlyweds, John and Jane Mason, struggle through their first year a marriage, plagued by money problems, illness, and a meddlesome live-in mother-in-law. To top it all off, their baby son is dying of pneumonia, and can only be saved by a serum that must be flown from Salt Lake City to New York.

programme.title: Darkness Visible
programme.desc: Murray, Ruth, and Dot are the only children from the orphanage left unclaimed for the holidays. After rescuing a dog caught in a trap, they find themselves in the magical house of Miss Angela Dwelf, a charming and uniquely talented woman.

programme.title: The Green Dress
programme.desc: 13-year-old Rosa feels unwelcome at the School of Performing Arts where she is bullied by the spiteful Lucy who is threatened by Rosa's talents and increasing popularity. Things change considerably when Rosa purchases a second-hand dress.

programme.title: First Flight: A Mother Hummingbird's Story
programme.desc: One day, one of nature’s smallest birds, a Black-chinned Hummingbird, built her nest atop a backyard clothesline. This enchanting and remarkably detailed film reveals the tireless efforts of the hummingbird mother who raises and cares for two chicks from their hatching to their leaving the nest.

programme.title: Book 5: The Mountain of Adventure (Part 1)
programme.desc: When the family visits Germany, Allison decides to paint while Bill works, and the children go on a pony trek with Hans. When the ponies become frightened and run from camp, Hans rides off in pursuit of them, but is knocked off his horse unconscious, leaving the children in a precarious situation.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis goes for a spin in a Lincoln Cosmo and Model A Rod.

programme.title: Swarm
programme.desc: Princess Vara has fallen ill, and the group is taken in by Harana, a healer and leader of a group called The Watchers. She leads them to a bountiful valley which does not seem to appear on any map. But it soon becomes evident that this idyllic valley is secretly controlled by Kreel.

programme.title: The 1930s
programme.desc: Though overshadowed by the Great Depression, there is no shortage of ingenuity in the 1930s. programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Top Redfish

programme.title: Flyway Extremes
programme.desc: From the heat of Louisiana to the north in Wisconsin, the duck action is hot at any temperature.

Benny Blanco and Capt. Albert Hernandez show the importance of protecting the Everglades for future generations.

programme.title: Ford Frontier Fishing

They take on bass in the back waters of eastern Texas on this episode of Fishing Frontiers.

programme.title: Burning Up the Bay
programme.desc: The Great Lakes are home to some of the best musky fisheries across North America. In summer, the muskies often establish a home range around large, shallow weed flats. Jim Saric and Pro Guide Bret Alexander encountered a pack of muskies on an overcast and rainy summer day and with the biometrics being high, they burned blades covering water quickly, trigging strikes from multiple muskies.

programme.title: Jack’s Lake Lunge
programme.desc: Jack’s Lake in Apsley, Ontario, Canada, is an overlooked sleeper musky water in the Kawartha Lakes region, but should not be ignored. In this summer strategy session, first, Jim Saric, along with musky hunters John Cowan and Pete Hoffmann, dissect Jack’s Lake in mid-summer. Then, Jim and Pro Guide Chris Taurisano utilize various casting techniques in pursuit of early-summer muskies.

programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a “normal” family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate – not once, but twice within two years – for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian émigré. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandro’s second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be “an American family" - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Sherman’s March), “with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all."

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

Andrew, who has Cerebral Palsy and uses a wheelchair, remembers the excitement of going to a gay bar for the first time and the reality that sets in once he arrives. Jason was a ballet dancer during most of his teenage years and into his 20s. He was celebrated for being thin. During one of his first times at a gay bar, he was told he's too skinny and needed to put on some muscle, leading him down a path of taking testosterone and being unhappy. It wasn't until he realized he needed to be happy with who he was because "I wasn’t happy pretending to be someone else." When Renee was a teen, a neighborhood mom noticed how Renee dressed and took them (Renee uses "they/them/their" pronouns) to The Gap to buy them feminine-looking pants. The experience was traumatic, but also transformational. programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. Portland isn’t afraid to remind us all that kink is political AF! From Strippers fighting for equal rights and pay amidst a pandemic to Foodie Activism for Sex Workers, Young connects with fellow sexual revolutionaries making a difference in their city. Madison’s explorations lead them to an amazing cast of characters including Nikeisah C. Newton, a chef turned sex worker activist, Cat Hollis - a stripper rights activist and organizer for the Portland Stripper’s Strike, Arabelle Raphael - sex worker and fetishist, and the donut daddy of our dreams, Dadi Iris, who shows us just what those donut holes are really for!

programme.title: Paolo Arrivabeni - ORW
programme.desc: L'opera è sinonimo di cantanti. Eppure l'orchestra sinfonica gioca un ruolo cruciale in queste opere musicali e teatrali. L'Orchestre Royal de Wallonie - Liège, sotto la direzione di Paolo Arrivabeni, ci introduce quindi alla ricchezza della musica strumentale di alcune opere.

programme.title: Symphonic Dances: Zahia Ziouani
programme.desc: A capo dell' Orchestra Sinfonica Divertimento (fondata nel 1998, in residenza a Stains dal 2005), Zahia Ziouani è riuscita a diversificare il pubblico della musica classica. Gli studenti dei conservatori della regione dell'Île-de-France si uniscono a lei per un viaggio nel repertorio sinfonico sotto il segno della danza, dalla tarantella italiana alla farandola provenzale, passando per il gopak ucraino.

programme.title: G. Puccini: Tosca - Simon Rattle
programme.desc: Basata su un'opera teatrale di Victorien Sardou, l'opera Tosca ha conquistato il pubblico sin dalla sua uscita nel 1900. Questo dramma verista è sublimato dalla composizione virtuosa di Puccini. - Sotto la direzione di Sir Simon Rattle, la storia d'amore di Floria Tosca e Mario Cavaradossi si svolge e viene messa alla prova dal tirannico capo della polizia Scarpia, che governa Roma. In questa produzione, il famoso tenore argentino Marcelo Álvarez trascende la scena, accompagnato dalla sublime Kristine Opolais nel ruolo dell'eroina.

programme.title: Outstanding Performers
programme.desc: Un’ora con i migliori artisti del momento: Barenboim, Repin, Lang Lang…

programme.title: Daniel Oren & Saioa Hernandez - ORW
programme.desc: L'affascinante soprano spagnolo Saioa Hernández, con la sua voce potente e ammaliante, interpreta le famose arie d'opera italiane in concerto. Questo spettacolo ci permette di apprezzare il bel canto "l'arte del canto lirico" utilizzato nelle opere dal XVII secolo. Valorizzando le capacità tecniche dei cantanti, a volte a scapito dell'espressione scenica, la voce vola come fosse un uccellino.

programme.title: B. Philharmoniker: Gershwin Night
programme.desc: Il Waldbühne di Berlino, residenza estiva dell'orchestra filarmonica della città, i Berliner Philharmoniker, è uno degli anfiteatri all'aperto più belli d'Europa. Nell'estate del 2003, il direttore d'orchestra giapponese Seji Ozawa ha diretto la famosa orchestra su successi di Gershwin come Un américain à Paris, Rhapsody in Blue, I Got Rhythm ... Ospite speciale: Il famoso trio jazz di Marcus Roberts.

programme.title: Vasily Petrenko: Dvořák - Beethoven
programme.desc: Una chiamata dal destino? Messaggi rivoluzionari segreti nascosti nella musica? La Quinta Sinfonia di Beethoven è una delle opere più esaminate nella storia della musica. Comunque la si interpreti, è senza dubbio una delle composizioni più potenti e magistrali mai scritte. Ascoltate questa sinfonia drammatica e commovente eseguita dalla Israel Philharmonic Orchestra sotto la raffinata direzione di Vasily Petrenko.

programme.title: Leonidas Kavakos And Yuja Wang
programme.desc: Due degli artisti più emblematici del Festival di Verbier interpretano insieme le opere di Brahms in un ricco concerto di musica da camera. Acclamato all'unanimità dal mondo della musica classica dal 1985, quando fece scalpore diventando il più giovane vincitore del prestigioso Concorso Sibelius, il violinista greco Leonidas Kavakos combina in questo concerto il suo virtuosismo con quello della pianista Yuja Wang, un'artista affermata a soli 26 anni.

programme.title: S. Prokofiev - Valery Gergiev
programme.desc: Il Festival di Pasqua di Mosca è uno degli eventi di musica classica più importanti al mondo. Vi sono presenti i più grandi solisti sotto alla direzione del più rinomato direttore d'orchestra russo, Valery Gergiev, con l'orchestra del Teatro Mariinsky di San Pietroburgo, di cui è il direttore. In un ciclo dedicato al compositore Sergei Prokofiev, il pianista russo Daniil Trifonov interpreta il Concerto per pianoforte e orchestra n. 1.

programme.title: Havana Danza, 2011
programme.desc: Quattro programmi allegri e appassionati compongono lo spettacolo "Havana Danza", che unisce teatro americano, danze afro-caraibiche e balletto classico europeo. Da oltre 50 anni la compagnia cubana "Danza Contemporanea" mette in scena danzatori di altissimo livello in uno stile crudo e mistico al tempo stesso. Oggi vanta una reputazione internazionale e oltre 70 produzioni nel suo repertorio.
